title: Ashtabula Address Points LBRS
description: The State of Ohio Location Based Response System address points depict the access points to addressable structures along public and private roads within participating Ohio Counties. title: Development Web Map
description: This interactive map includes recent and current development activities. Data sources, currency and other information are displayed by selecting map features. Contact MORPC to add information to this map.

title: Points Of Interest
description: All Category/Type combinations for MORPC Points of Interest data, for 15-counties in Central Ohio, showing places of commercial activity, transportation, public places, hospitals, industrial (landfills, waste transfer stations, quarries, wastewater and water treatment), group quarters, government locations, and public places. Geography: 15 county Central Ohio region: Delaware, Fairfield, Fayette, Franklin, Hocking, Knox, Licking, Logan, Madison, Marion, Morrow, Perry, Pickaway, Ross, and Union Counties. Source: Sources vary by point category and type. Query source attribute on a specific point for more.

description:

title: Metropolitan Transportation Plan 2016-2040 Web Map
description: The Metropolitan Transportation Plan (MTP) is the long-range transportation plan for Central Ohio. This interactive map includes transportation projects anticipated to occur by the year 2040 that will use federal transportation funds. The plan was developed by MORPC.

title: SFY 2018-2021 Transportation Improvement Program Web Map
description: The TIP interactive map is designed to receive comments on MORPC's Draft Transportation Improvement Program for State Fiscal Years 2018-2021. The TIP is a schedule of transportation improvements in the MORPC transportation planning area. The TIP includes investments in highways, public transit, bikeways, pedestrian facilities, bridges, traffic signals and other aspects of the transportation system over a four-year period. It also includes planning and engineering studies that may lead to construction in later years.
